  "texts": [
    "The paper also briefly explains how MCDM works in financial management.",
    "Comparatively, a significant analysis was presented by Aouni (2009), where the author linked portfolio optimization with multiattribute portfolio selection.",
    "In his further research (Aouni, 2010; Aouni et al., 2008), the author gave more examples of how goal programming can be used in portfolio selection.",
    "A comprehensive review of MCDM techniques was presented in the study Mardani et al. (2015), where a list of publications (more than 460) with different applications in many fields of science, engineering and management was provided.",
    "Among them are such techniques as AHP (Forman and Gass, 2001), PROMETHEE (Brans, 1982), ELECTRE (Roy, 1968), TOPSIS (Hwang and Yoon, 1981), ANP (Saaty, 1996), VIKOR (Yu, 1973), and hybrid MCDM (Shyur and Shih, 2006)."
  ],
